<div id="review_3048996067" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3048996067" />
    <a title="Linda Power" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/90672154-linda-power"><img alt="Linda Power" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3048996067?book_show_action=true">Nov 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Linda Power" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Linda Power" href="/user/show/90672154-linda-power">Linda Power</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3048996067" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16822310537912945218">Wow. What an awesome debut novel. Loved Gerry Fegan as the anti hero. He is dark and gritty while haunted by his past. The past is the what he did during the Troubles in Belfast during the 70’s and 80’s. He is trying to resolve the nightmares and guilt from that period. No hero’s in this story that had lots of twists and turns. Look forward to a follow up.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

